Label: Number and Quantity
fullstatement: Relationships among number representations, including whole numbers, fractions, decimals, integers, rational and irrational numbers, complex numbers, and quantities represented in vectors and matrices.

Label: Operations, Algebra, and Functions
fullstatement: Processes to perform operations with numbers, simplify expressions, and solve equations, and the relationships among operations, patterns, and functions.

Label: Geometry and Measurement
fullstatement: The properties and measurements of and relationships among two and three dimensional shapes

Label: Statistics and Probability
fullstatement: Processes to calculate and interpret chance, distributions, descriptive statistics, and inferential statistics.

Label: Counting and Cardinality
fullstatement: The order of the number words, application of counting principles, and skills to compare the quantities in sets

Label: Quantity Estimation
fullstatement: Approximating the number of objects in a set

Label: Whole Numbers
fullstatement: The names, cardinal size, and structure of non-decimal numbers in the base ten system, naming and comparing whole numbers, and performing operations with whole numbers

Label: Fraction Concepts
fullstatement: The value and representations of numbers expressible in the form a/b where a and b are whole numbers

Label: Decimals
fullstatement: Numbers represented as fractions with denominators that are powers of ten (e.g., 7/100 = 0.07)

Label: Signed Numbers
fullstatement: Understanding numbers which may be less than zero.

Label: Real and Complex Numbers
fullstatement: Understand and use numbers outside of the rational number system
Citations Text: Rachlin & NCTM, 2006

Label: Vectors and Matrices
fullstatement: representing sets of numbers in vectors and matrices
Citations Text: Neudecker, Zmyslony, & Trenkler, 2003; Van Deventer & Wittmann, 2007

Label: Pre-Counting
fullstatement: understanding numbers as they relate to quantities

Label: Number List
fullstatement: reciting in order the number words to 100, and identifying and writing numerals to 20

Label: Count Sets
fullstatement: instantly recognizing sets of 0-10 and counting larger sets of objects

Label: Compare and Order
fullstatement: Compare and order quantities, written numbers, and ordinal positions

Label: Counting by Powers of Ten
fullstatement: counting forwards and backwards by powers of 10

Label: Counting Techniques
fullstatement: Counting large numbers of objects, including combinations and permutations
